      "writtenOn": "2017-05-26T12:25:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The use of the fColorSpace field was a somewhat unique implementation to avoid early raster of pictures.  Typically, we choose not to remember to the color space.  Ex: we can do what you\u0027ve done here, but not pass the color space to the new SkColorFilter.  Obviously this means that calling onMakeColorSpace() twice is a bad idea since the src is always sRGB...",
